The press briefing by White House Press Secretary Josh Earnest on July 25, 2016 covered a range of topics including the Democratic National Convention, the investigation into the DNC email hack, the possibility of Russia's involvement in the hack, President Obama's endorsement of Kamala Harris, Donald Trump's statements about the World Trade Organization, Tim Kaine's position on the Trans-Pacific Partnership, the President's endorsement of Hillary Clinton, the situation in Syria and Aleppo, the admission of Syrian refugees into the US, nuclear weapons policy, civilian casualties in Afghanistan, the recent attacks in Germany, and the situation in Turkey.